<br>
Actually, that applies to a lot of epics Xarp. Cleric epic, only bottleneck is Rage. If he is up (hehe, good luck but if you can say it for the wiz stuff...), it is very easy. And they drop the pieces everytime so nothing to worry about.<br>
<br>
Enchanter epic, same. Rogue epic, same. If you are going to have it just be mobs are all up and drop the pieces needs, a large portion of the epics can be completed quite fast. Unfortunately, if you rely on normal drop rates, chances are decent you won't complete the wiz one where you would the others if the mobs were all up. <p>Qaman<BR>
Sorcerer - Eternal Wrath<BR>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaktarmythmaker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AktarMythmaker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 11:19:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heh</span><hr size=1> I'm glad I have the epic, the effect just gets better every day I use it.  Most classes envy my epic.  But when it first came out, I didn't even work on it because I knew how Verant does quests (that's another story).  When it was found to be Cazic's skin on the wizard epic, I chuckled, and shrugged off ever getting it.  Then when I saw that maybe the golems would be dropping cazic skin, I thought-- well, maybe it will happen one day.<br>
<br>
Then VS stopped being so heavily contested, and I've always liked Kedge anyway.  So suddenly it was just a matter of finding the timing on the broken golem and not having anyone else go for him.  Not terribly difficult.<br>
<br>
However... this quest is exactly what is wrong with a majority of quests in EQ.  Contested mobs.  Random drops.  Spawn times.<br>
<br>
I would much rather have a long, involved, difficult quest that I knew I could accomplish, if I just planned a little on getting people together for necessary parts.<br>
<br>
I don't agree with &quot;opportunity&quot; EQ... never have.<br>
<br>
I wish every battle for each piece of everyone's epic required gobs of people to kill each triggered (or 4 hours spawn) mob.  Organization and friends should be the bottleneck to the completion of epics... not politics and luck.<br>
<br>
The parts of Epic quests that I like?  Taking a raid down into the Hole to kill mobs that spawn every 4 hours, doing a triggered mob that requires a good number of people (I think most of those should be harder though, in general-- requiring 4-5 groups of all level 60s minimum-- more people if less levels, etc).<br>
<br>
The parts of Epic quests I don't like?  Level 52 clerics camping Ragefire for days straight and getting killed on a random Nagafen pop (actually, I sort of like that, because it makes me laugh at the insanity).<br>
<br>
In short, I totally disagree with Verant's vision that limiting the influx of items should be determined by spawn times and drop tables.  Epic items should be limited by desire, planning, organization, levels, and skill.  In short, make the battles tougher.  Have specific strategies.  Require more people.  Put them deep in dungeons.<br>
<br>
I picture young Arthur running by that old church, frantically looking for a sword to help Sir Kay and having someone walk out saying &quot;just got my Excalibur, if you need one for the tourney, it should 'pop' in about 7 hours-- have fun and good luck!&quot;<br>
<br>
/boggle <p><center>    <b>Aktar Mythmaker <b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/useverinewolfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Severine Wolfe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 12:00:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.clan-donald.com/screenshots/severine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heh</span><hr size=1> The Enraged Golem was the easiest in my opinion.  Took us 20 minutes of pure melee but we only lost one person and we had cleared Fear at the time so I was off to get the Staff of Gabstick, which totally rocks... hope I can get another after the epic is done LOL<br>
